snippet.title: Ready Play Movies #30 - Lawsuit, No Firing, and Possible Hiring
snippet.description:
After a week off, Luis and Troy meet to talk about two weeks worth of movie news, including Scarlet Johannson suing Disney for breach of contract, WB is not firing Amber Heard, Jungle Cruise flopping at the box office, and Netflix wants to hire Christopher Nolan.  Plus thoughts on Old, Still Water, the new Venom trailer, and all the movie anniversaries.  All this and more!

00:00 - Intro / Housekeeping
06:50 - Back to the Future (Movie Anniversaries)
42:14 - Old
49:35 - Still Water
52:44 - The Boy Behind The Door
58:08 - The Bad Batch
1:01:39 Scar Jo Lawsuit Against Disney
1:14:40 Jungle Cruise Flops at the Box Office
1:22:13 WB Never Considered Replacing Amber Heard
1:30:06 Netflix wants Christoper Nolan
1:36:18 - Extra News
1:52:16 - Check This Out!
2:08:28 - Netflix and Chill (Netflix/iTunes/Amazon top 10 chart & recommendations)
2:13:19 - New Releases (Suicide Squad /Val)
2:20:35 - Outro (theme song)
 
Every Tuesday, Luis Menchaca (@chacalaca88) and Troy Bracy (@bracytroy58) will catch you up on everything that’s new and exciting in the world of movies. If you want to write anything to be read in the show, email readyplaymovies@gmail.com or hit us up on Twitter @readyplaymovies.
